Find the year anchor. Starting with year 2026:
 - note the century anchor A = Tuesday
 - take the last two digits T = Y % 100 = 2026 % 100 = 26
 - if odd, add eleven T = T + (T % 2)*11 = 26 + (26 % 2)*11 = 26
 - then divide by two T = T / 2 = 26 / 2 = 13
 - if odd, add eleven T = T + (T % 2)*11 = 13 + (13 % 2)*11 = 24
 - subtract from seven T = 7 - T = 7 - 24 = -17 ≡ Thursday
 - add the century anchor to get W = A + T = Tuesday + Thursday = 6 ≡ Saturday
